<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idc345f63d-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87" identifier="/us/usc/t38/s2407"><num value="2407">§ 2407.</num><heading> Authority to accept and maintain suitable memorials</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Subject to such restrictions as the Secretary may prescribe, the Secretary may accept gifts, devises, or bequests from legitimate societies and organizations or reputable individuals, made in any manner, which are made for the purpose of beautifying national cemeteries, or are determined to be beneficial to such cemetery. The Secretary may make land available for this purpose, and may furnish such care and maintenance as the Secretary deems necessary.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idc345f63e-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87">(Added <ref href="/us/pl/93/43/s2/a">Pub. L. 93–43, § 2(a)</ref>, <date date="1973-06-18">June 18, 1973</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/87/78">87 Stat. 78</ref>, § 1007; amended <ref href="/us/pl/99/576/tVII/s701/58">Pub. L. 99–576, title VII, § 701(58)</ref>, <date date="1986-10-28">Oct. 28, 1986</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/100/3296">100 Stat. 3296</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/101/237/tIII/s313/b/1">Pub. L. 101–237, title III, § 313(b)(1)</ref>, <date date="1989-12-18">Dec. 18, 1989</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/103/2077">103 Stat. 2077</ref>; renumbered § 2407, <ref href="/us/pl/102/83/s5/a">Pub. L. 102–83, § 5(a)</ref>, <date date="1991-08-06">Aug. 6, 1991</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/105/406">105 Stat. 406</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
